- The integer array parameter `arr` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `arr` length is greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to 100000.
- All values in the integer array parameter `arr` are greater than or equal to 1 and are less than or equal to 10000.
- The integer parameter `k` is greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to the length of the integer array parameter `arr`.
- The integer parameter `threshold` is greater than or equal to 0 and is less than or equal to 10000.
- The integer result is the number of sub-arrays of size `k` and average greater than or equal to `threshold`.